deploy update: client needed to stand up a GAE instance outside their network (the original was inside the VPN, thus didn’t serve correctly). That should be done imminently, and then I’ll redeploy everything.
what was issue serving from within the VPN?

2 things: 1) content partners can’t get to any of it from outside, including the CMS Admin, which would be a showstopper for them once they switched over and 2) we were having issues with endpoints 404ing, likely because of various redirects and how the VPN is handling auth.
it needed to be outside the VPN anyway, so we’re not going to waste any time bottoming out on 2)
alright, ready to go, deployed and ready for James to QA.
